<article>
<h2>Velocity Mixed mode</h2>
<form><textarea id="code" name="code">
##this is a velocity file that also contains html, css and javascript
<div class="main"><!-- some html -->
#if ($who)
	<p class="title">hello $who</p>
#else 
	<p class="title">hello world</p>
#end

<script>//some javascript
	var code = 'JS';
	alert("And here is some "+code+" code");
</script>
<style>/* some css */
.title {
	font-size: 24px;
	font-weight: bold;
	color: #f00;
}
</style>
</textarea></form>

    <script>
      var editor = CodeMirror.fromTextArea(document.getElementById("code"), {
        lineNumbers: true,
        matchBrackets: true,
        mode: "velocitymixed",
        indentUnit: 4,
        indentWithTabs: true,
        enterMode: "keep",
        tabMode: "shift"
      });
    </script>

    <p>Simple Velocity Mixed mode (supports HTML, XML, CSS, Javascript) which was built by taking HTML Mixed mode and mixing in Velocity. Depends on HTMLMixed, XML, JavaScript, CSS and Velocity modes.</p>

    <p><strong>Mode defined as:</strong> <code>"velocitymixed"</code>.</p>
